HEADWORD: My
<hw>My</hw> <pr>(m⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>a. & poss. pron.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>mi</ets>, fr. <ets>min</ets>. See <er>Mine</er>, and cf., for loss
of <it>n</it>, <er>A</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, <er>An</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Of or belonging to me; -- used always
attributively; <as>as, <ex>my</ex> body; <ex>my</ex> book</as>; --
<xex>mine</xex> is used in the predicate; <as>as, the book is
<ex>mine</ex></as>. See <er>Mine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

